WFS, Your efforts to find out about your brother are courageous and commendable. There can be some good that comes out of the tragedy of his death. It is important that we all rassle with the effects of our nation's decision to go to war. And you can find some peace in knowing you did what you could to know and honor your brother. Class Lass' comments make sense. There are many resources online and at the National Archives which can help you learn about your brother's life and death in VN, and the character of the men he served with. Take care.
